# Repo-root .dockerignore — applies to every `docker build` whose
# context is the repo root (relay, website, test-peer). Without this,
# the cargo `target/` dir (~86 GB) gets shipped to the daemon as build
# context on every build, taking minutes and wasting bandwidth.
#
# Each subdirectory's Dockerfile is COPY'd in via `COPY . .` after a
# cargo-chef recipe step, so we only need to exclude things that are
# never useful inside the build context.

# Cargo build output — by far the largest offender.
target/
**/target/

# Dioxus build output for the website.
**/dist/

# Editor / IDE state
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp

# Local Docker compose state (relay, etc.)
**/secrets/
**/.env
**/.env.*

# OS junk
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Git history is not needed inside the image.
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Test scratch + bench outputs
/tmp_bench_results/
**/*.db
**/*.db-shm
**/*.db-wal
**/*.sqlite
**/*.sqlite-shm
**/*.sqlite-wal

# Markdown is needed for the website (compile-time include_str!) but
# not for relay or test-peer. We'd rather the website carries its
# content/ via explicit COPY lines — easier to audit. Default: drop
# all .md, then re-allow the website's content/ in case someone uses
# a wildcard COPY in the website Dockerfile.
*.md
!README.md
!website/content/**/*.md
!website/README.md

# Node / web tooling junk if anything ever lands
node_modules/
.cache/
